					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If IP for some good SMS titles could be obtained, i don't think the effort is entirely futile. People still play the NES to some extent, while the SMS lacks the same popular status (i'm geographically biased, of course). But it'd still involve lots of work, not least making the graphics look good. Also possible, but about as much manual labour as drawing graphics for an all-new game.<br /><br />There'd be possibilities expanding on the background music in pleasant ways.<br /><br /><br />I personally see less point in porting a NES title to SMS as you'd take a game from a system (relatively) many have and use, moving it to a less common system, but if the goal is to simply exercise your brain and have a bit of fun, i guess either would do.<br /><br />I mean, there's a homebrew that plays mostly like simon's quest for the zx spectrum.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
